article.headline: Weber St. 34, N. Arizona 31
article.story: OGDEN, Utah -- C.J. Tuckett set Weber State's single game all-purpose yards record with 407 yards and three touchdowns as Weber State rallied in the final minute for a 34-31 victory over Northern Arizona Saturday. The junior tailback, who entered the game with 197 yards rushing on the season, ran for 254 yards and added 144 in the return game. Mike Hoke scored the go-ahead touchdown with 26 seconds remaining to snap a three-game losing streak for Weber State (4-6, 4-3 Big Sky). Northern Arizona (4-6, 3-5) attempted a hook-and-ladder play on the game's final play, but came up short after three laterals. Cary Grosshart passed for 294 yards and two touchdowns, Khalil Paden had 152 receiving yards and Zach Bauman rushed for 126 yards and two scores for Northern Arizona.
